  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quality & Process Controller",
  "description": "<p><u>Candidate Role</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>We are looking for motivated and organised individual who can improve the Company’s process flow system.</li>\n  <li>The Candidate will be stationed at Customer’s facility to monitor the daily operations and document the work procedures for systematic and structured training of staffs working at the facility.</li>\n  <li>The candidate shall have a keen eye to detect any potential error that may occur and rectify it pre-emptively.</li>\n  <li>This position is to uphold the Customer’s perception of the Company’s quality of services – logistics.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Job Responsibilities</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure all services and documentation are delivered to customer’s specification.</li>\n  <li>Ensure work flows and operation processes are in line with written procedures, and practical trainings.</li>\n  <li>Conduct policing checks on ground, specifically inside cleanroom, to ensure handling, packing, protection processes are carried out according to approved training/document.</li>\n  <li>Develop quality tracking matrices and provide timely reports to the affected clients.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that goods, accessories and associated tools are packed in accordance to respective work instructions.</li>\n  <li>Review/maintain work instructions and other technical documents to provide timely and relevant update. Be the custodian of quality/process flow related documents.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that good housekeeping is practised throughout every operation. Spearhead the implementation of continuous improvement program, for cleanroom logistic processes.</li>\n  <li>Execute error prevention initiatives, or any plan to meet Customer’s quality expectation.</li>\n  <li>Review and eliminate unnecessary appraisal/documentation to streamline the processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Job Requirements</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office. Shared Point.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Written and Verbal Communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Ability to adapt and multi-task.</li>\n  <li>Relevant work experience in logistics, semi-conductor or electronic industry is an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Able to write in a clear, concise manner, and generate comprehensive reports is an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Candidates who are keened to pick up documentation skills, through on-the-job training, are welcome to apply.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Job Location: Woodlands</p>",
